A protein that is a translation product of the Escherichia coli K-12 qseC gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. QseC is the sensor kinase component of the QseB-QseC two-component system, which is one component of the quorum-sensing regulatory cascade involved in the regulation of flagella and motility genes. QseBC modulates transcription of flhDC, the master regulator for flagella and motility genes.
